On 18 September 2020, in Valencia, Carabobo state, a group of doctors and nurses from the City Hospital Dr. Enrique Tejera protested to demand the release of a doctor who was arrested for the illegal trade of medicines for coronavirus. Protesters informed that the doctor is innocent. This was the second day of protests. [size=no report]
On 18 September 2020, in Tucupita, Delta Amacuro state, a group of merchants blocked a road to demand the distribution of fuel. [size=no report]

On 18 September 2020, in Maracaibo, Zulia state, members of a suspected organized criminal group threw an explosive toward the clinic Paraiso. 3 people were injured during the explosion. There are no reports on the identity of the perpetrators nor crime motivation. No fatalities.

On 17 September 2020, in Cabimas, Zulia state, active workers and pensioners from the state oil company PDVSA protested due to low salaries and the lack of medical insurance, on the Independencia Avenue. [size=no report]

On 17 September 2020, in Maracaibo, Zulia state, at least 50 residents from various communities including San Jacinto and Ziruma protested in front of the office of the state electric company Corpoelec to demand electric power, in the El Amparo sector. On 17 September 2020, in Valencia, Carabobo state, a group of doctors and nurses from the City Hospital Dr. Enrique Tejera protested to demand the release of a doctor who was arrested for the illegal trade of medicines for coronavirus.
